1
00:00:54,555 --> 00:00:57,892
<i>FLYNN". This is the story of how I died.</i>

2
00:00:59,435 --> 00:01:04,023
<i>But don't worry, this is a fun story,
and the truth is, it isn't even mine.</i>

3
00:01:04,106 --> 00:01:07,109
<i>This is the story of a girl
named Rapunzel.</i>

4
00:01:08,819 --> 00:01:10,529
<i>And it starts with the sun.</i>

5
00:01:12,406 --> 00:01:17,036
<i>Once upon a time, a single drop
of sunlight fell from the heavens.</i>

6
00:01:17,119 --> 00:01:22,792
<i>And from this small drop of sun
grew a magic golden flower.</i>

7
00:01:23,709 --> 00:01:26,921
<i>It had the ability to heal
the sick and injured.</i>

8
00:01:28,422 --> 00:01:31,967
<i>Oh, you see that old woman over there?
You might want to remember her.</i>

9
00:01:32,051 --> 00:01:33,052
<i>She's kind of important.</i>

10
00:01:34,845 --> 00:01:36,847
<i>Centuries passed</i>

11
00:01:36,889 --> 00:01:39,183
<i>and a hop, skip and a boat ride away
there grew a kingdom.</i>

12
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:43,312
<i>The kingdom was ruled
by a beloved king and queen.</i>

13
00:01:44,230 --> 00:01:46,941
<i>And the queen
was about to have a baby.</i>

14
00:01:47,608 --> 00:01:48,692
<i>But she got sick.</i>

15
00:01:49,777 --> 00:01:50,778
<i>Really sick.</i>

16
00:01:51,529 --> 00:01:52,863
<i>She was running out of time,</i>

17
00:01:52,905 --> 00:01:55,991
<i>and that's when people
start to look for a miracle.</i>

18
00:01:56,075 --> 00:01:59,411
<i>Or in this case, a magic golden flower.</i>

19
00:01:59,912 --> 00:02:02,665
<i>Ah! I told you she'd be important.</i>

20
00:02:02,748 --> 00:02:05,042
<i>Instead of sharing the sun's gift,</i>

21
00:02:05,084 --> 00:02:07,795
<i>this woman, Mother Gothel,
hoarded its healing power</i>

22
00:02:07,878 --> 00:02:11,215
<i>and used it to keep herself young
for hundreds of years.</i>

23
00:02:11,257 --> 00:02:14,760
<i>And all she had to do
was sing a special song.</i>

24
00:02:15,469 --> 00:02:19,139
<i>(SINGING) Flower, gleam and glow</i>

25
00:02:19,807 --> 00:02:23,602
<i>Let your power shine</i>

26
00:02:24,103 --> 00:02:27,356
<i>Make the clock reverse</i>

27
00:02:27,439 --> 00:02:31,277
<i>Bring back what once was mine</i>

28
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:34,572
<i>What once was mine</i>

29
00:02:34,613 --> 00:02:38,450
<i>FLYNN: You get the gist. She sings to it,
she turns young. Creepy, right?</i>

30
00:02:38,576 --> 00:02:40,327
(VOICES APPROACHING)

31
00:02:49,587 --> 00:02:50,629
We found it!

32
00:02:56,802 --> 00:03:01,473
FLYNN: <i>The magic of the golden flower
healed the queen.</i>

33
00:03:02,308 --> 00:03:07,313
<i>A healthy baby girl, a princess
was born, with beautiful golden hair.</i>

34
00:03:07,354 --> 00:03:08,981
(BABY COOING HAPPILY)

35
00:03:09,023 --> 00:03:10,399
(CHUCKUNG)

36
00:03:11,317 --> 00:03:12,443
(COOING)

37
00:03:15,029 --> 00:03:16,280
(LAUGHING SOFTLY)

38
00:03:16,322 --> 00:03:18,991
<i>FLYNN". I'll give you a hint,
that's Rapunzel.</i>

39
00:03:19,074 --> 00:03:20,284
(GIGGLES)

40
00:03:20,951 --> 00:03:22,244
<i>To celebrate her birth,</i>

41
00:03:22,328 --> 00:03:25,664
<i>the king and queen
launched a flying lantern into the sky.</i>

42
00:03:25,706 --> 00:03:29,501
(PEOPLE CHEERING)

43
00:03:31,086 --> 00:03:34,298
<i>And for that one moment,
everything was perfect.</i>

44
00:03:37,217 --> 00:03:38,761
<i>And then that moment ended.</i>

45
00:03:40,512 --> 00:03:44,600
<i>(SINGING) Flower, gleam and glow</i>

46
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:50,189
<i>Let your power shine</i>

47
00:03:50,564 --> 00:03:52,358
<i>Make the clock...</i>

48
00:03:52,524 --> 00:03:53,734
(GASPS)

49
00:03:58,155 --> 00:03:59,198
(RAPUNZEL CRYING)

50
00:03:59,239 --> 00:04:01,742
FLYNN: <i>Gothel broke into the castle,
stole the child,</i>

51
00:04:01,825 --> 00:04:03,869
<i>and just like that, gone!</i>

52
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:09,500
<i>The kingdom searched and searched,
but they could not find the princess.</i>

53
00:04:09,792 --> 00:04:12,878
<i>For deep within the forest,
in a hidden tower,</i>

54
00:04:12,962 --> 00:04:14,463
<i>Gothel raised the child as her own.</i>

55
00:04:14,630 --> 00:04:17,383
<i>RAPUNZEL: (SINGING)
Save what has been lost</i>

56
00:04:17,549 --> 00:04:21,428
<i>Bring back what once was mine</i>

57
00:04:21,512 --> 00:04:24,139
<i>What once was mine</i>

58
00:04:24,223 --> 00:04:26,850
<i>FLYNN: Gothel had found
her new magic flower,</i>

59
00:04:26,892 --> 00:04:29,603
<i>but this time,
she was determined to keep it hidden.</i>

60
00:04:30,229 --> 00:04:32,815
Why can't I go outside?

61
00:04:32,898 --> 00:04:35,567
The outside world is a dangerous place,

62
00:04:35,609 --> 00:04:38,153
filled with horrible, selfish people.

63
00:04:38,237 --> 00:04:41,323
You must stay here, where you're safe.

64
00:04:41,407 --> 00:04:43,033
Do you understand, flower?

65
00:04:43,075 --> 00:04:44,451
Yes, Mommy.

66
00:04:47,746 --> 00:04:52,292
FLYNN: <i>But the walls of that tower
could not hide everything.</i>

67
00:04:55,587 --> 00:04:57,089
<i>Each year, on her birthday,</i>

68
00:04:57,131 --> 00:05:00,718
<i>the king and queen released
thousands of lanterns into the sky</i>

69
00:05:00,759 --> 00:05:05,848
<i>in hope that one day
their lost princess would return.</i>

70
00:05:22,406 --> 00:05:23,741
(WHIMPERS)

71
00:05:24,742 --> 00:05:26,160
Ha!

72
00:05:26,869 --> 00:05:27,953
Hmm.

73
00:05:28,287 --> 00:05:31,790
Well, I guess
Pascal's not hiding out here.

74
00:05:32,666 --> 00:05:33,917
(SNIGGERING)

75
00:05:34,793 --> 00:05:36,003
- Gotcha!
-(SCREAMS)

76
00:05:36,378 --> 00:05:37,588
(PANTS)

77
00:05:37,713 --> 00:05:42,259
That's 22 for me.
How about 23 out of 45?

78
00:05:43,677 --> 00:05:45,804
Okay. Well, what do you want to do?

79
00:05:46,013 --> 00:05:47,306
(SQUEAKS)

80
00:05:48,599 --> 00:05:53,395
Yeah. I don't think so.
I like it in here, and so do you.

81
00:05:55,564 --> 00:05:58,901
Oh, come on, Pascal.
It's not so bad in there.

82
00:06:11,538 --> 00:06:15,042
<i>(SINGING) Seven a.m., the usual
morning lineup</i>

83
00:06:15,959 --> 00:06:20,172
<i>Start on the chores
And sweep till the floor's all clean</i>

84
00:06:20,672 --> 00:06:24,301
<i>Polish and wax, do laundry
and mop and shine up</i>

85
00:06:24,343 --> 00:06:28,806
<i>Sweep again and by then it's, like, 7:15</i>

86
00:06:28,847 --> 00:06:33,310
<i>And so I'll read a book
Or maybe two or three</i>

87
00:06:33,352 --> 00:06:37,648
<i>I'll add a few new paintings
to my gallery</i>

88
00:06:37,689 --> 00:06:42,027
<i>I'll play guitar and knit
and cook and basically</i>

89
00:06:42,111 --> 00:06:46,657
<i>Just wonder when will my life begin?</i>

90
00:06:55,999 --> 00:07:00,212
<i>Then after lunch it's puzzles
and darts and baking</i>

91
00:07:00,295 --> 00:07:04,758
<i>Papier-méché, a bit of ballet and chess</i>

92
00:07:05,092 --> 00:07:08,679
<i>Pottery and ventriloquy, candle-making</i>

93
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:13,433
<i>Then I'll stretch, maybe sketch
Take a climb, sew a dress</i>

94
00:07:13,517 --> 00:07:17,479
<i>And I'll reread the books
If I have time to spare</i>

95
00:07:17,563 --> 00:07:21,942
<i>I'll paint the walls some more
I'm sure there's room somewhere</i>

96
00:07:22,025 --> 00:07:26,405
<i>And then I'll brush and brush
and brush and brush my hair</i>

97
00:07:26,488 --> 00:07:31,076
<i>Stuck in the same place
I've always been</i>

98
00:07:31,118 --> 00:07:36,165
<i>And I'll keep wondering and wondering
and wondering and wondering</i>

99
00:07:36,248 --> 00:07:39,626
<i>When will my life begin?</i>

100
00:07:41,587 --> 00:07:45,007
<i>Tomorrow night</i>

101
00:07:45,174 --> 00:07:49,344
<i>the lights will appear</i>

102
00:07:50,053 --> 00:07:53,307
<i>Just like they do</i>

103
00:07:53,390 --> 00:07:58,228
<i>on my birthday each year</i>

104
00:07:59,730 --> 00:08:03,025
<i>What is it like</i>

105
00:08:04,109 --> 00:08:08,030
<i>out there where they glow</i>

106
00:08:09,114 --> 00:08:12,743
<i>Now that I'm older</i>

107
00:08:13,285 --> 00:08:17,789
<i>Mother might just let me go</i>

108
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:44,650
Wow! I could get used
to a view like this.

109
00:08:44,691 --> 00:08:46,610
Rider, come on!

110
00:08:46,652 --> 00:08:51,907
Hold on. Yep. I'm used to it.
Guys, I want a castle.

111
00:08:52,366 --> 00:08:55,202
We do this job,
you can buy your own castle.

112
00:09:05,379 --> 00:09:06,672
(SNEEZES)

113
00:09:07,589 --> 00:09:09,591
- Hay fever?
- Yeah.

114
00:09:11,593 --> 00:09:12,678
Huh?

115
00:09:13,262 --> 00:09:16,181
Wait! Hey, wait!

116
00:09:17,015 --> 00:09:19,810
Can't you picture me in a castle
of my own? Because I certainly can.

117
00:09:19,851 --> 00:09:22,729
All the things we've seen,
and it's only 8:00 in the morning!

118
00:09:22,813 --> 00:09:25,899
Gentlemen, this is a very big day!

119
00:09:26,275 --> 00:09:30,362
(SIGHS) This is it!
This is a very big day, Pascal.

120
00:09:30,404 --> 00:09:31,446
(CHUCKLES)

121
00:09:31,530 --> 00:09:34,533
I'm finally going to do it.
I'm going to ask her.

122
00:09:34,616 --> 00:09:36,702
- GOTH EL: Rapunzel!
-(GASPS)

123
00:09:37,202 --> 00:09:38,870
Let down your hair!

124
00:09:39,830 --> 00:09:40,872
It's time!

125
00:09:42,165 --> 00:09:45,460
I know, I know.
Come on. Don't let her see you.

126
00:09:47,754 --> 00:09:51,758
Rapunzel!
I'm not getting any younger down here!

127
00:09:52,634 --> 00:09:54,177
Coming, Mother!

128
00:10:13,989 --> 00:10:17,242
(GRUNTING)

129
00:10:18,410 --> 00:10:21,038
(PANTING) Hi. Welcome home, Mother.

130
00:10:21,079 --> 00:10:24,374
(EXCLAIMS) Rapunzel,
how you manage to do that

131
00:10:24,416 --> 00:10:27,586
every single day without fail.

132
00:10:27,669 --> 00:10:30,088
It looks absolutely exhausting, darling.

133
00:10:30,172 --> 00:10:32,591
Oh, (CHUCKLES) it's nothing.

134
00:10:32,632 --> 00:10:34,926
Then I don't know why it takes so long.

135
00:10:35,010 --> 00:10:37,429
(LAUGHS) Oh, darling, I'm just teasing.

136
00:10:37,971 --> 00:10:39,306
(CHUCKLES)

137
00:10:39,806 --> 00:10:40,932
All right.

138
00:10:41,016 --> 00:10:44,353
So, Mother, as you know
tomorrow is a very big day...

139
00:10:44,436 --> 00:10:46,021
Rapunzel, look in that mirror.

140
00:10:46,104 --> 00:10:47,606
You know what I see?

141
00:10:47,647 --> 00:10:51,735
I see a strong, confident,
beautiful young lady.

142
00:10:52,861 --> 00:10:55,030
Oh, look, you're here, too. (LAUGHS)

143
00:10:55,113 --> 00:10:58,533
I'm just teasing.
Stop taking everything so seriously.

144
00:10:59,201 --> 00:11:02,079
Okay. So, Mother,
as I was saying, tomorrow is...

145
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:04,623
Rapunzel,
Mother's feeling a little run-down.

146
00:11:04,664 --> 00:11:07,667
Would you sing for me, dear?
Then we'll talk.

147
00:11:07,751 --> 00:11:10,087
Oh! Of course, Mother.

148
00:11:18,428 --> 00:11:19,805
<i>(QUICKLY) Flower, gleam and glow
Let your power shine</i>

149
00:11:19,888 --> 00:11:21,556
<i>Make the clock reverse
Bring back what once was mine</i>

150
00:11:21,640 --> 00:11:23,433
<i>Heal what has been hurt
Change the Fates' design</i>

151
00:11:23,475 --> 00:11:25,560
<i>Save what has been lost
Bring back what once was mine</i>

152
00:11:25,644 --> 00:11:27,396
- Rapunzel!
- So, Mother,

153
00:11:27,479 --> 00:11:30,315
earlier I was saying tomorrow
is a big day, and you didn't respond.

154
00:11:30,399 --> 00:11:33,151
So, I'm just going to tell you,
it's my birthday! (LAUGHS)

155
00:11:33,235 --> 00:11:36,154
- Ta-da!
- No, no, no. Can't be.

156
00:11:36,238 --> 00:11:39,616
I distinctly remember.
Your birthday was last year.

157
00:11:39,658 --> 00:11:42,994
That's the funny thing about birthdays.
They're kind of an annual thing.

158
00:11:43,078 --> 00:11:44,079
(SIGHS)

159
00:11:44,830 --> 00:11:49,334
Mother, I'm turning 18,
and I wanted to ask...

160
00:11:49,793 --> 00:11:52,504
(SIGHS) What I really want
for this birthday...

161
00:11:52,629 --> 00:11:55,006
Actually what I wanted
for quite a few birthdays now...

162
00:11:55,048 --> 00:11:57,217
Rapunzel, please,
stop with the mumbling.

163
00:11:57,300 --> 00:11:59,928
You know how I feel about
the mumbling. Blah-blah-blah-blah.

164
00:12:00,011 --> 00:12:02,681
It's very annoying!
I'm just teasing. You're adorable.

165
00:12:02,764 --> 00:12:04,599
I love you so much, darling.

166
00:12:05,851 --> 00:12:07,227
(PASCAL SQUEAKS)

167
00:12:10,439 --> 00:12:12,107
(EXCLAIMS) I want to see
the floating lights.

168
00:12:13,733 --> 00:12:15,902
(CHUCKLES) What?

169
00:12:15,986 --> 00:12:19,781
I was hoping you would take me
to see the floating lights.

170
00:12:20,157 --> 00:12:22,951
Oh! You mean the stars.

171
00:12:23,243 --> 00:12:24,536
That's the thing.

172
00:12:25,954 --> 00:12:28,874
I've charted stars,
and they're always constant.

173
00:12:28,957 --> 00:12:32,836
But these, they appear every year
on my birthday, Mother.

174
00:12:32,878 --> 00:12:34,880
Only on my birthday.

175
00:12:34,921 --> 00:12:40,093
And I can't help but feel like
they're meant for me.

176
00:12:40,927 --> 00:12:42,888
I need to see them, Mother.

177
00:12:42,929 --> 00:12:46,475
And not just from my window, in person.

178
00:12:46,558 --> 00:12:49,186
I have to know what they are.

179
00:12:49,227 --> 00:12:53,315
You want to go outside?
(SCOFFS) Why, Rapunzel...

180
00:12:53,940 --> 00:12:56,860
<i>(SINGING) Look at you,
as fragile as a flower</i>

181
00:12:57,569 --> 00:13:01,406
<i>Still a little sapling, just a sprout</i>

182
00:13:01,490 --> 00:13:04,367
<i>You know why we stay up in this tower</i>

183
00:13:04,409 --> 00:13:06,036
- I know, but...
- That's right.

184
00:13:06,077 --> 00:13:09,956
<i>To keep you safe and sound, dear</i>

185
00:13:10,040 --> 00:13:12,751
<i>Guess I always knew
this day was coming</i>

186
00:13:13,710 --> 00:13:16,421
<i>Knew that soon
you'd want to leave the nest</i>

187
00:13:17,088 --> 00:13:18,340
<i>Soon but not yet</i>

188
00:13:18,590 --> 00:13:20,926
<i>Shh!
Trust me, pet</i>

189
00:13:21,259 --> 00:13:25,096
<i>Mother knows best</i>

190
00:13:25,972 --> 00:13:27,265
(HATCH THUDDING CLOSED)

191
00:13:27,432 --> 00:13:30,519
<i>Mother knows best
Listen to your mother</i>

192
00:13:30,602 --> 00:13:31,603
(SCREAMS)

193
00:13:31,686 --> 00:13:33,563
<i>It's a scary world out there</i>

194
00:13:33,605 --> 00:13:35,190
<i>Mother knows best</i>

195
00:13:35,273 --> 00:13:36,274
(GRUNTING)

196
00:13:36,316 --> 00:13:38,276
<i>One way or another
Something will go wrong</i>

197
00:13:38,318 --> 00:13:39,986
<i>I swear</i>

198
00:13:40,070 --> 00:13:42,864
<i>Ruffians, thugs, poison ivy, quicksand</i>

199
00:13:42,948 --> 00:13:45,075
<i>Cannibals and snakes, the plague</i>

200
00:13:45,116 --> 00:13:46,243
- No!
- Yes.

201
00:13:46,284 --> 00:13:48,954
<i>Also large bugs
Men with pointy teeth</i>

202
00:13:49,037 --> 00:13:52,457
<i>And stop! No more, you'll just upset me</i>

203
00:13:52,541 --> 00:13:55,585
<i>Mother's right here
Mother will protect you</i>

204
00:13:55,627 --> 00:13:58,922
<i>Darling, here's what I suggest</i>

205
00:13:58,964 --> 00:14:03,134
<i>Skip the drama
Stay with Mama</i>

206
00:14:03,218 --> 00:14:08,014
<i>Mother knows best</i>

207
00:14:08,139 --> 00:14:09,391
(LAUGHS)

208
00:14:10,267 --> 00:14:13,103
<i>Mother knows best
Take it from your mumsy</i>

209
00:14:13,144 --> 00:14:15,981
<i>On your own, you won't survive</i>

210
00:14:16,064 --> 00:14:18,984
<i>Sloppy, underdressed
Immature, clumsy</i>

211
00:14:19,067 --> 00:14:21,945
<i>Please, they'll eat you up alive</i>

212
00:14:21,987 --> 00:14:25,156
<i>Gullible, naive
Positively grubby</i>

213
00:14:25,240 --> 00:14:27,993
<i>Ditsy and a bit... Well, hmm, vague</i>

214
00:14:28,076 --> 00:14:30,954
<i>Plus, I believe, getting kind of chubby</i>

215
00:14:30,996 --> 00:14:35,125
<i>I'm just saying 'cause I wuv you</i>

216
00:14:35,166 --> 00:14:38,253
<i>Mother understands
Mother's here to help you</i>

217
00:14:38,336 --> 00:14:43,592
<i>All I have is one request</i>

218
00:14:47,679 --> 00:14:50,307
- Rapunzel?
- Yes?

219
00:14:51,683 --> 00:14:55,604
Don't ever ask to leave this tower again.

220
00:14:57,564 --> 00:14:58,857
Yes, Mother.

221
00:14:59,357 --> 00:15:00,400
Oh.

222
00:15:00,859 --> 00:15:03,111
I love you very much, dear.

223
00:15:03,820 --> 00:15:05,405
I love you more.

224
00:15:05,697 --> 00:15:07,866
I love you most.

225
00:15:09,034 --> 00:15:11,202
<i>(SINGING) Don't forget it</i>

226
00:15:11,244 --> 00:15:14,914
<i>You'll regret it</i>

227
00:15:14,998 --> 00:15:19,502
<i>Mother knows best</i>

228
00:15:23,548 --> 00:15:26,718
Ta-ta! I'll see you in a bit, my flower!

229
00:15:29,095 --> 00:15:30,555
I'll be here.

230
00:15:47,781 --> 00:15:49,032
(PANTING)

231
00:15:52,744 --> 00:15:53,953
(GASPS)

232
00:15:54,162 --> 00:15:55,497
Oh, no.

233
00:15:55,580 --> 00:15:58,166
No,no,no,no,no.
This is bad. This is very, very bad.

234
00:15:58,208 --> 00:15:59,918
This is really bad.

235
00:16:01,336 --> 00:16:03,421
They just can't get my nose right.

236
00:16:03,505 --> 00:16:04,881
Who cares?

237
00:16:04,964 --> 00:16:08,093
It's easy for you to say.
You guys look amazing.

238
00:16:09,052 --> 00:16:12,514
(HORSES NEIGHING)

239
00:16:17,936 --> 00:16:19,229
(PANTING)

240
00:16:23,441 --> 00:16:26,277
All right. Okay.
Give me a boost and I'll pull you up.

241
00:16:27,779 --> 00:16:29,239
Give us the satchel first.

242
00:16:29,280 --> 00:16:30,490
(EXCLAIMS)

243
00:16:30,615 --> 00:16:31,825
I just...

244
00:16:32,033 --> 00:16:36,037
I can't believe that after all we've been
through together, you don't trust me?

245
00:16:38,456 --> 00:16:39,582
Ouch.

246
00:16:42,377 --> 00:16:46,047
(GRUNTING)

247
00:16:47,841 --> 00:16:49,509
Now help us up, pretty boy!

248
00:16:49,592 --> 00:16:52,470
Sorry, my hands are full.

249
00:16:53,471 --> 00:16:54,597
What?

250
00:16:55,265 --> 00:16:56,307
Rider!

251
00:16:57,600 --> 00:16:58,977
(EXCLAIMS)

252
00:17:02,814 --> 00:17:04,899
Retrieve that satchel at any cost!

253
00:17:04,983 --> 00:17:06,276
SOLDIERS: Yes, sir!

254
00:17:06,735 --> 00:17:08,111
(NEIGHING)

255
00:17:11,448 --> 00:17:12,699
(GRUNTS)

256
00:17:12,824 --> 00:17:13,825
(GASPS)

257
00:17:22,834 --> 00:17:25,378
We got him now, Maximus.

258
00:17:30,592 --> 00:17:31,676
(GRUNTS)

259
00:17:32,594 --> 00:17:33,678
(URGES HORSE)

260
00:17:33,762 --> 00:17:34,888
(LAUGHS)

261
00:17:36,681 --> 00:17:37,849
(SNORTS)

262
00:17:38,183 --> 00:17:40,769
(GRUNTS) Come on, fleabag! Forward!

263
00:17:43,188 --> 00:17:44,689
No. No!

264
00:17:45,106 --> 00:17:50,320
Stop it! Stop it!
Give it to me! Give me that!

265
00:18:16,346 --> 00:18:17,347
Ha!

266
00:18:17,388 --> 00:18:18,389
(CRACKING)

267
00:18:19,015 --> 00:18:20,975
(NEIGHING IN ALARM)

268
00:18:24,229 --> 00:18:25,355
-(SCREAMS)
-(NEIGHS)

269
00:18:32,320 --> 00:18:33,321
(SPITS)

270
00:18:37,534 --> 00:18:38,910
(SNIFFING)

271
00:18:52,131 --> 00:18:53,424
(EXCLAIMS)

272
00:18:53,591 --> 00:18:55,260
(MAXIMUS NEIGHING)

273
00:18:57,178 --> 00:18:58,221
(SNORTS)

274
00:18:59,889 --> 00:19:00,932
(NICKERS)

275
00:19:20,076 --> 00:19:24,372
(GRUNTING)

276
00:19:27,625 --> 00:19:29,127
(PANTING)

277
00:19:32,463 --> 00:19:33,965
Alone at last.

278
00:19:34,132 --> 00:19:35,425
(CLANGING)

279
00:19:36,676 --> 00:19:37,969
(SQUEALS)

280
00:20:18,343 --> 00:20:19,344
Huh.

281
00:20:25,224 --> 00:20:26,726
(GASPS SOFTLY)

282
00:20:35,610 --> 00:20:36,736
- Huh?
%GAsPs)

283
00:20:36,819 --> 00:20:38,947
(CLANGING)

284
00:20:40,406 --> 00:20:43,368
(GRUNTING)

285
00:20:43,743 --> 00:20:45,036
(PANTING)

286
00:20:46,496 --> 00:20:48,206
(GRUNTING)

287
00:20:48,247 --> 00:20:49,248
(EXCLAIMS)

288
00:20:54,754 --> 00:20:55,838
Hmm.

289
00:20:57,799 --> 00:20:59,133
(CHUCKLING CONTENTEDLY)

290
00:20:59,217 --> 00:21:00,218
(SQUEALS)

291
00:21:00,385 --> 00:21:02,720
(GRUNTING)

292
00:21:05,098 --> 00:21:06,099
Huh?

293
00:21:09,560 --> 00:21:12,897
Okay, okay, okay.
I've got a person in my closet.

294
00:21:12,939 --> 00:21:15,525
I've got a person in my closet.

295
00:21:16,776 --> 00:21:20,613
(ENUNCIATING)
I've got a person in my closet!

296
00:21:20,697 --> 00:21:22,031
(CHUCKLES)

297
00:21:23,282 --> 00:21:25,910
Too weak to handle myself out there,
huh, Mother?

298
00:21:25,952 --> 00:21:29,080
Well, tell that to my frying pan.

299
00:21:29,580 --> 00:21:30,915
(GROANS)

300
00:21:31,416 --> 00:21:32,417
Huh?

301
00:21:42,635 --> 00:21:43,678
Hmm.

302
00:21:51,310 --> 00:21:52,311
Hmm.

303
00:22:10,621 --> 00:22:12,331
- GOTH EL: Rapunzel!
-(GASPS) Oh!

304
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:15,835
Let down your hair!

305
00:22:16,377 --> 00:22:17,795
One moment, Mother!

306
00:22:17,837 --> 00:22:19,881
I have a big surprise!

307
00:22:19,964 --> 00:22:22,300
Uh... I do, too!

308
00:22:22,341 --> 00:22:24,677
Ooh, I bet my surprise is bigger!

309
00:22:24,969 --> 00:22:27,346
(SOFTLY) I seriously doubt it.

310
00:22:28,681 --> 00:22:32,143
I brought back parsnips. I'm going
to make hazelnut soup for dinner.

311
00:22:32,185 --> 00:22:34,604
Your favorite. Surprise!

312
00:22:34,645 --> 00:22:37,065
Well, Mother,
there's something I want to tell you.

313
00:22:37,148 --> 00:22:39,984
Oh, Rapunzel, you know I hate
leaving you after a fight.

314
00:22:40,068 --> 00:22:42,528
Especially when I've clone
absolutely nothing wrong.

315
00:22:42,612 --> 00:22:44,989
I've been thinking a lot
about what you said earlier.

316
00:22:45,031 --> 00:22:47,575
I hope you're not still talking
about the stars.

317
00:22:47,658 --> 00:22:50,078
"Floating lights,"
and, yes, I'm leading up to that.

318
00:22:50,161 --> 00:22:52,663
Because I really thought
we dropped the issue, sweetheart.

319
00:22:52,747 --> 00:22:54,832
No, Mother, I'm just saying,

320
00:22:54,916 --> 00:22:57,418
you think I'm not strong enough
to handle myself out there.

321
00:22:57,502 --> 00:23:00,755
Oh, I know you're not strong enough
to handle yourself out there.

322
00:23:00,838 --> 00:23:04,133
- But if you just...
- We're done talking about this.

323
00:23:04,175 --> 00:23:06,719
- Trust me! I know what I'm...
- Rapunzel.

324
00:23:06,803 --> 00:23:09,347
- Oh, come on!
- Enough with the lights!

325
00:23:09,430 --> 00:23:13,851
You are not leaving this tower! Ever!

326
00:23:19,398 --> 00:23:23,861
(GROANS) Great. Now I'm the bad guy.

327
00:23:36,332 --> 00:23:39,210
All I was going to say, Mother, is that...

328
00:23:39,919 --> 00:23:42,630
I know what I want for my birthday now.

329
00:23:42,713 --> 00:23:44,715
And what is that?

330
00:23:45,133 --> 00:23:46,467
New paint.

331
00:23:47,135 --> 00:23:50,471
The paint made from the white shells
you once brought me.

332
00:23:50,555 --> 00:23:55,726
That is a very long trip, Rapunzel.
Almost three days' time.

333
00:23:55,977 --> 00:24:01,065
I just thought it was a better idea
than the stars.

334
00:24:02,733 --> 00:24:03,901
(SIGHS)

335
00:24:05,194 --> 00:24:07,530
You'll be all right on your own?

336
00:24:08,364 --> 00:24:11,075
I know I'm safe as long as I'm here.

337
00:24:19,083 --> 00:24:21,586
<i>GOTHEL: I'll be back
in three days' time.</i>

338
00:24:22,545 --> 00:24:24,797
<i>I love you very much, dear.</i>

339
00:24:25,756 --> 00:24:27,091
<i>RAPUNZEL: I love you more.</i>

340
00:24:28,092 --> 00:24:30,261
<i>GOTHEL: I love you most.</i>

341
00:24:48,404 --> 00:24:50,740
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

342
00:24:50,948 --> 00:24:51,949
Okay.

343
00:25:08,216 --> 00:25:09,467
Huh.

344
00:25:22,230 --> 00:25:23,648
(SQUEAKING)

345
00:25:29,654 --> 00:25:30,905
(EXCLAIMS)

346
00:25:30,988 --> 00:25:32,114
Huh? What...

347
00:25:33,866 --> 00:25:35,243
(GRUNTING)

348
00:25:37,870 --> 00:25:40,623
FLYNNI Is this hair?

349
00:25:41,332 --> 00:25:44,543
Struggling... Struggling is pointless.

350
00:25:44,627 --> 00:25:45,670
Huh?

351
00:25:45,836 --> 00:25:47,546
(RAPUNZEL CLAMBERING DOWN)

352
00:25:48,089 --> 00:25:52,677
I know why you're here,
and I'm not afraid of you.

353
00:25:53,135 --> 00:25:54,679
What?

354
00:26:03,020 --> 00:26:06,899
Who are you?
And how did you find me?

355
00:26:07,858 --> 00:26:09,110
(STAMMERING SOFTLY)

356
00:26:10,361 --> 00:26:13,698
(ENUNCIATING) Who are you,
and how did you find me?

357
00:26:15,616 --> 00:26:17,034
(CLEARS THROAT)

358
00:26:17,118 --> 00:26:21,205
I know not who you are,
nor how I came to find you.

359
00:26:21,289 --> 00:26:23,207
But may I just say...

360
00:26:24,542 --> 00:26:26,294
Hi.

361
00:26:28,546 --> 00:26:31,257
How you doing?
The name's Flynn Rider.

362
00:26:32,842 --> 00:26:34,677
How's your day going? Huh?

363
00:26:34,719 --> 00:26:35,761
(GRUNTS IN CONFUSION)

364
00:26:36,053 --> 00:26:39,724
Who else knows my location,
Flynn Rider?

365
00:26:39,807 --> 00:26:41,934
- All right, blondie.
- Rapunzel.

366
00:26:42,018 --> 00:26:43,728
<i>Gesundheit. Here's the deal.</i>

367
00:26:43,769 --> 00:26:46,689
I was in a situation,
gallivanting through the forest.

368
00:26:46,731 --> 00:26:49,066
I came across your tower and...

369
00:26:49,108 --> 00:26:50,401
Oh! Oh, no.

370
00:26:50,568 --> 00:26:51,777
Where is my satchel?

371
00:26:52,069 --> 00:26:55,281
I've hidden it.
Somewhere you'll never find it.

372
00:26:58,242 --> 00:27:00,077
It's in that pot, isn't it?

373
00:27:00,786 --> 00:27:02,121
(CLANGING)

374
00:27:02,455 --> 00:27:04,457
(GROANING)

375
00:27:04,790 --> 00:27:06,000
Huh?

376
00:27:06,292 --> 00:27:08,753
(EXCLAIMS) Would you stop that?

377
00:27:08,794 --> 00:27:11,672
Now it's hidden
where you'll never find it.

378
00:27:12,506 --> 00:27:16,510
So, what do you want with my hair?
To cut it?

379
00:27:16,594 --> 00:27:17,845
- What?
- Sell it?

380
00:27:17,928 --> 00:27:21,599
No! Listen, the only thing
I want to do with your hair

381
00:27:21,682 --> 00:27:24,060
is to get out of it, literally.

382
00:27:24,101 --> 00:27:25,186
You...

383
00:27:25,269 --> 00:27:27,938
Wait. You don't want my hair?

384
00:27:27,980 --> 00:27:29,940
Why on earth would I want your hair?

385
00:27:30,024 --> 00:27:32,651
Look, I was being chased,
I saw a tower, I climbed it.

386
00:27:32,735 --> 00:27:33,778
End of story.

387
00:27:33,819 --> 00:27:35,321
(STAMMERING) You're telling the truth?

388
00:27:35,446 --> 00:27:36,739
Yes!

389
00:27:36,947 --> 00:27:38,032
Hmm.

390
00:27:39,867 --> 00:27:42,453
(GROWLING)

391
00:27:45,623 --> 00:27:47,124
(GROWLING)

392
00:27:49,001 --> 00:27:50,044
(SQUEAKING)

393
00:27:50,127 --> 00:27:52,004
(WHISPERING) I know.
I need someone to take me.

394
00:27:52,088 --> 00:27:54,632
-(SQUEAKING)
- I think he's telling the truth, too.

395
00:27:54,673 --> 00:27:57,843
He doesn't have fangs.
But what choice do I have?

396
00:27:58,511 --> 00:27:59,637
(SIGHS)

397
00:27:59,720 --> 00:28:03,724
Okay, Flynn Rider,
I'm prepared to offer you a deal.

398
00:28:03,808 --> 00:28:05,643
- Deal?
- Look this way.

399
00:28:05,684 --> 00:28:07,061
(EXCLAIMING)

400
00:28:07,144 --> 00:28:10,022
Do you know what these are?

401
00:28:10,106 --> 00:28:13,234
You mean the lantern thing
they do for the princess?

402
00:28:13,818 --> 00:28:17,238
Lanterns? I knew they weren't stars.

403
00:28:18,322 --> 00:28:20,658
Well, tomorrow evening,

404
00:28:20,741 --> 00:28:24,662
they will light the night sky
with these lanterns.

405
00:28:24,703 --> 00:28:28,332
You will act as my guide,
take me to these lanterns,

406
00:28:28,374 --> 00:28:30,000
and return me home safely.

407
00:28:30,042 --> 00:28:34,380
Then, and only then,
will I return your satchel to you.

408
00:28:34,463 --> 00:28:35,673
That is my deal.

409
00:28:35,756 --> 00:28:36,924
Yeah.

410
00:28:37,007 --> 00:28:38,050
(GRUNTING)

411
00:28:38,134 --> 00:28:39,593
No can do.

412
00:28:39,677 --> 00:28:43,514
Unfortunately the kingdom and I
aren't exactly simpatico at the moment,

413
00:28:43,556 --> 00:28:45,850
so I won't be taking you anywhere.

414
00:28:52,440 --> 00:28:55,651
Something brought you here,
Flynn Rider.

415
00:28:55,693 --> 00:28:57,153
Call it what you will,

416
00:28:57,194 --> 00:29:00,030
-fate, destiny...
- A horse.

417
00:29:00,114 --> 00:29:02,450
So I have made the decision
to trust you.

418
00:29:02,533 --> 00:29:03,576
A horrible decision, really.

419
00:29:03,659 --> 00:29:06,745
But trust me when I tell you this.

420
00:29:08,706 --> 00:29:12,209
You can tear this tower apart
brick by brick,

421
00:29:12,251 --> 00:29:17,006
but without my help, you will never find
your precious satchel.

422
00:29:17,089 --> 00:29:18,466
(CLEARS THROAT)

423
00:29:18,549 --> 00:29:19,884
Let me get this straight.

424
00:29:19,967 --> 00:29:23,220
I take you to see the lanterns,
bring you back home,

425
00:29:23,262 --> 00:29:25,139
and you'll give me back my satchel?

426
00:29:25,222 --> 00:29:26,724
I promise.

427
00:29:28,559 --> 00:29:33,272
And when I promise something,
I never, ever break that promise.

428
00:29:35,649 --> 00:29:37,651
- Even
-(SQUEAKS IN AGREEMENT)

429
00:29:40,279 --> 00:29:42,656
All right, listen.
I didn't want to have to do this,

430
00:29:42,740 --> 00:29:44,492
but you leave me no choice.

431
00:29:45,242 --> 00:29:47,119
Here comes the smolder.

432
00:29:54,668 --> 00:29:58,714
This is kind of an off day for me.
This doesn't normally happen.

433
00:29:58,756 --> 00:30:00,591
Fine! I'll take you to see the lanterns.

434
00:30:00,633 --> 00:30:02,009
Really?

435
00:30:03,010 --> 00:30:04,053
Oops.

436
00:30:04,094 --> 00:30:06,096
(GASPING) You broke my smolder.

437
00:30:06,931 --> 00:30:10,184
(GRUNTING)

438
00:30:11,602 --> 00:30:13,604
Are you coming, blondie?

439
00:30:23,489 --> 00:30:27,201
<i>(SINGING) Look at the world so close
And I'm halfway to it</i>

440
00:30:28,452 --> 00:30:32,540
<i>Look at it all so big
Do I even dare</i>

441
00:30:33,457 --> 00:30:37,336
<i>Look at me, there at last
I just have to do it</i>

442
00:30:38,003 --> 00:30:42,132
<i>Should I? No
Here I go</i>

443
00:30:43,717 --> 00:30:44,760
(GRUNTS)

444
00:30:44,802 --> 00:30:46,178
(CHUCKLES)

445
00:30:51,225 --> 00:30:54,812
(LAUGHING)

446
00:31:09,243 --> 00:31:11,620
(LAUGHING)

447
00:31:13,038 --> 00:31:18,627
<i>Just smell the grass, the dirt
Just like I dreamed they'd be</i>

448
00:31:20,045 --> 00:31:25,384
<i>Just feel that summer breeze
The way it's calling me</i>

449
00:31:25,593 --> 00:31:26,719
(GASPS)

450
00:31:27,052 --> 00:31:32,391
<i>For, like, the first time ever
I'm completely free</i>

451
00:31:33,809 --> 00:31:37,688
<i>I could go running and racing</i>

452
00:31:37,771 --> 00:31:39,690
<i>And dancing and chasing</i>

453
00:31:39,982 --> 00:31:43,819
<i>And leaping and bounding
Hair flying, heart pounding</i>

454
00:31:43,861 --> 00:31:48,032
<i>And splashing and reeling
and finally feeling</i>

455
00:31:48,991 --> 00:31:55,080
<i>That's when my life begins</i>

456
00:32:02,546 --> 00:32:05,549
I can't believe I did this!

457
00:32:05,633 --> 00:32:07,926
(GASPS) I can't believe I did this.

458
00:32:08,010 --> 00:32:10,721
(LAUGHING) I can't believe I did this!

459
00:32:12,348 --> 00:32:14,224
Mother would be so furious.

460
00:32:14,266 --> 00:32:17,645
But that's okay. What she doesn't know
won't kill her, right?

461
00:32:17,728 --> 00:32:20,522
(CRYING) Oh, my gosh!
This would kill her.

462
00:32:20,689 --> 00:32:23,942
This is so fun!

463
00:32:24,401 --> 00:32:27,279
I am a horrible daughter.
I'm going back.

464
00:32:27,655 --> 00:32:29,990
(LAUGHING) I am never going back!

465
00:32:31,450 --> 00:32:34,161
I am a despicable human being!

466
00:32:34,328 --> 00:32:35,704
(WHOOPING)

467
00:32:36,372 --> 00:32:38,791
Best day ever!

468
00:32:41,794 --> 00:32:43,545
(CRYING)

469
00:32:45,422 --> 00:32:46,590
(CLEARS THROAT)

470
00:32:47,883 --> 00:32:51,303
You know,
I can't help but notice you seem

471
00:32:51,387 --> 00:32:53,931
a little at war with yourself here.

472
00:32:54,765 --> 00:32:57,393
- What?
- I'm only picking up bits and pieces.

473
00:32:57,434 --> 00:33:01,105
Overprotective mother,
forbidden road trip. This is serious stuff.

474
00:33:01,730 --> 00:33:04,817
But let me ease your conscience.
This is part of growing up.

475
00:33:04,900 --> 00:33:09,113
A little rebellion, a little adventure,
that's good. Healthy, even.

476
00:33:10,698 --> 00:33:12,116
(CHUCKLES) You think?

477
00:33:12,199 --> 00:33:15,369
I know. You're way over-thinking this,
trust me.

478
00:33:15,452 --> 00:33:17,496
Does your mother deserve it? No.

479
00:33:17,579 --> 00:33:20,499
Would this break her heart
and crush her soul? Of course.

480
00:33:20,582 --> 00:33:22,668
But you've got to do it.

481
00:33:23,502 --> 00:33:25,045
"Break her heart"?

482
00:33:25,504 --> 00:33:28,132
- In half.
-"Crush her soul"?

483
00:33:29,133 --> 00:33:30,342
Like a grape.

484
00:33:30,426 --> 00:33:33,470
She would be heartbroken. You're right.

485
00:33:33,512 --> 00:33:37,057
I am, aren't I? Oh, bother.

486
00:33:37,725 --> 00:33:42,146
All right. I can't believe I'm saying this,
but I'm letting you out of the deal.

