<i>Just how blind I've been</i>

978
01:07:28,044 --> 01:07:32,591
<i>Now I'm here, blinking in the starlight</i>

979
01:07:33,091 --> 01:07:37,012
<i>Now I'm here, suddenly I see</i>

980
01:07:37,387 --> 01:07:42,100
<i>Standing here, it's, oh, so clear</i>

981
01:07:42,142 --> 01:07:46,771
<i>I'm where I'm meant to be</i>

982
01:07:46,813 --> 01:07:51,109
<i>And at last I see the light</i>

983
01:07:51,443 --> 01:07:55,447
<i>And it's like the fog has lifted</i>

984
01:07:56,114 --> 01:08:00,702
<i>And at last I see the light</i>

985
01:08:00,785 --> 01:08:04,581
<i>And it's like the sky is new</i>

986
01:08:05,415 --> 01:08:10,086
<i>And it's warm and real and bright</i>

987
01:08:10,128 --> 01:08:15,467
<i>And the world has somehow shifted</i>

988
01:08:18,470 --> 01:08:23,391
<i>All at once, everything looks different</i>

989
01:08:23,475 --> 01:08:27,771
<i>Now that I see you</i>

990
01:08:33,151 --> 01:08:34,277
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

991
01:08:34,569 --> 01:08:37,072
I have something for you, too.

992
01:08:37,447 --> 01:08:40,659
I should have given it to you before,
but I was just scared.

993
01:08:40,992 --> 01:08:45,580
And the thing is, I'm not scared
anymore. You know what I mean?

994
01:08:47,457 --> 01:08:49,668
I'm starting to.

995
01:08:53,713 --> 01:08:58,260
<i>FLYNN". All those days
chasing down a daydream</i>

996
01:08:58,677 --> 01:09:02,472
<i>All those years, living in a blur</i>

997
01:09:03,014 --> 01:09:07,602
<i>All that time, never truly seeing</i>

998
01:09:07,686 --> 01:09:11,356
<i>Things the way they were</i>

999
01:09:12,440 --> 01:09:17,279
<i>Now she's here, shining in the starlight</i>

1000
01:09:17,362 --> 01:09:21,366
<i>Now she's here, suddenly I know</i>

1001
01:09:21,866 --> 01:09:26,496
<i>If she's here, it's crystal clear</i>

1002
01:09:26,538 --> 01:09:30,667
<i>I'm where I'm meant to go</i>

1003
01:09:30,709 --> 01:09:35,297
<i>BOTH: And at last I see the light</i>

1004
01:09:35,380 --> 01:09:39,551
<i>And it's like the fog has lifted</i>

1005
01:09:39,593 --> 01:09:43,930
<i>And at last I see the light</i>

1006
01:09:44,014 --> 01:09:48,143
<i>And it's like the sky is new</i>

1007
01:09:48,393 --> 01:09:53,064
<i>And it's warm and real and bright</i>

1008
01:09:53,106 --> 01:09:58,570
<i>And the world has somehow shifted</i>

1009
01:10:01,615 --> 01:10:06,661
<i>All at once, everything is different</i>

1010
01:10:06,745 --> 01:10:12,250
<i>Now that I see you</i>

1011
01:10:15,712 --> 01:10:17,881
<i>Now that I...</i>

1012
01:10:18,923 --> 01:10:22,302
see you

1013
01:10:41,905 --> 01:10:44,616
ls everything okay?

1014
01:10:44,658 --> 01:10:45,700
Huh?

1015
01:10:46,576 --> 01:10:48,370
Oh, yes. (CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

1016
01:10:48,703 --> 01:10:51,539
Yes, of course. I just...

1017
01:10:57,295 --> 01:10:59,631
I'm sorry. Everything is fine.

1018
01:11:00,173 --> 01:11:02,258
There's just something
I have to take care of.

1019
01:11:05,136 --> 01:11:06,221
Okay.

1020
01:11:07,972 --> 01:11:09,766
I'll be right back.

1021
01:11:13,978 --> 01:11:15,271
(SQUEAKS)

1022
01:11:15,939 --> 01:11:17,816
It's all right, Pascal.

1023
01:11:25,198 --> 01:11:27,117
FLYNN: Ah! There you are!

1024
01:11:27,158 --> 01:11:29,786
I've been searching everywhere
for you guys since we got separated.

1025
01:11:29,828 --> 01:11:34,082
The sideburns are coming in nice, huh?
Got to be excited about that.

1026
01:11:36,334 --> 01:11:37,711
(CLEARS THROAT)

1027
01:11:37,794 --> 01:11:40,547
Anyhow, I just wanted to say
I shouldn't have split.

1028
01:11:40,630 --> 01:11:44,426
The crown is all yours. I'll miss you,
but I think it's for the

1029
01:11:45,051 --> 01:11:46,094
best

1030
01:11:47,762 --> 01:11:51,182
Holding out on us again, eh, Rider?

1031
01:11:51,641 --> 01:11:54,561
- What?
- We heard you found something.

1032
01:11:54,644 --> 01:11:57,522
Something much more valuable
than a crown.

1033
01:11:58,523 --> 01:12:01,359
We want her instead.

1034
01:12:10,493 --> 01:12:11,536
(EXHALES)

1035
01:12:11,619 --> 01:12:14,873
I was starting to think you ran off
with the crown and left me.

1036
01:12:21,921 --> 01:12:23,548
He did.

1037
01:12:23,673 --> 01:12:26,885
What? No. He wouldn't.

1038
01:12:27,844 --> 01:12:29,512
See for yourself.

1039
01:12:34,392 --> 01:12:35,477
Eugene?

1040
01:12:38,188 --> 01:12:40,106
Eugene!

1041
01:12:42,358 --> 01:12:47,322
A fair trade. A crown
for the girl with the magic hair.

1042
01:12:48,531 --> 01:12:52,327
How much do you think someone would
pay to stay young and healthy forever?

1043
01:12:52,410 --> 01:12:55,330
No. Please. No!

1044
01:12:56,080 --> 01:12:57,123
No!

1045
01:13:00,251 --> 01:13:01,419
(SCREAMS)

1046
01:13:02,378 --> 01:13:03,880
-(THUDDING)
-(MEN GRUNTING)

1047
01:13:04,923 --> 01:13:06,216
GOTH EL: Rapunzel!

1048
01:13:07,926 --> 01:13:09,344
Mother?

1049
01:13:11,513 --> 01:13:13,890
(PANTING)

1050
01:13:14,224 --> 01:13:16,726
Oh, my precious girl!

1051
01:13:17,602 --> 01:13:18,853
Mother.

1052
01:13:19,395 --> 01:13:21,773
Are you all right? Are you hurt?

1053
01:13:21,856 --> 01:13:25,443
- How did you...
- I was so worried about you, dear.

1054
01:13:25,485 --> 01:13:29,072
So I followed you.
And I saw them attack you and...

1055
01:13:29,113 --> 01:13:31,783
Oh, my. Let's go before they come to!

1056
01:13:59,060 --> 01:14:00,937
(CRYING)

1057
01:14:01,980 --> 01:14:05,942
You were right, Mother.
You were right about everything.

1058
01:14:07,110 --> 01:14:10,488
I know, darling. I know.

1059
01:14:16,160 --> 01:14:18,413
(BOAT HULL CREAKING)

1060
01:14:20,415 --> 01:14:22,458
(SCRAPING)

1061
01:14:24,335 --> 01:14:25,420
Look!

1062
01:14:26,004 --> 01:14:27,380
The crown!

1063
01:14:28,214 --> 01:14:29,507
(GROGGILY) Rapunzel.

1064
01:14:30,174 --> 01:14:31,593
- Rapunzel!
-(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

1065
01:14:33,678 --> 01:14:36,431
- FLYNN: No! Wait, guys!
-(NICKERS QUESTIONINGLY)

1066
01:14:39,267 --> 01:14:41,019
FLYNN: Rapunzel!

1067
01:14:57,452 --> 01:14:58,661
(DOOR OPENS)

1068
01:15:00,246 --> 01:15:02,373
Let's get this over with, Rider.

1069
01:15:04,459 --> 01:15:05,793
Where are we going?

1070
01:15:09,464 --> 01:15:10,506
Oh.

1071
01:15:13,635 --> 01:15:16,387
There. It never happened.

1072
01:15:18,640 --> 01:15:23,561
Now, wash up for dinner.
I'm making hazelnut soup.

1073
01:15:27,357 --> 01:15:33,363
(SIGHS) I really did try, Rapunzel.
I tried to warn you what was out there.

1074
01:15:34,030 --> 01:15:38,493
The world is dark and selfish and cruel.

1075
01:15:38,576 --> 01:15:41,579
If it finds
even the slightest ray of sunshine,

1076
01:15:42,497 --> 01:15:44,248
it destroys it.

1077
01:15:57,470 --> 01:16:01,933
(SQUEAKING SADLY)

1078
01:16:07,605 --> 01:16:09,607
(SIGHS)

1079
01:17:08,791 --> 01:17:10,043
(GROANS)

1080
01:17:23,347 --> 01:17:24,682
(GRUNTING)

1081
01:17:26,976 --> 01:17:29,187
How did you know about her?
Tell me, now!

1082
01:17:29,228 --> 01:17:32,065
It wasn't us! It was the old lady!

1083
01:17:32,148 --> 01:17:33,399
Om lady?

1084
01:17:33,733 --> 01:17:34,817
(GRUNTS)

1085
01:17:34,859 --> 01:17:37,028
Wait. No! Wait!

1086
01:17:37,111 --> 01:17:40,031
You don't understand!
She's in trouble! Wait!

1087
01:17:40,364 --> 01:17:41,532
Rapunzel?

1088
01:17:43,242 --> 01:17:45,036
What's going on up there?

1089
01:17:45,244 --> 01:17:48,706
(PANTING)

1090
01:17:49,207 --> 01:17:50,875
Are you all right?

1091
01:17:52,210 --> 01:17:53,753
I'm the lost princess.

1092
01:17:53,878 --> 01:17:57,632
(SIGHS) Please speak up, Rapunzel.
You know how I hate the mumbling.

1093
01:17:57,715 --> 01:18:00,551
(LOUDLY) I am the lost princess.

1094
01:18:00,635 --> 01:18:02,303
Aren't I?

1095
01:18:04,472 --> 01:18:06,724
Did I mumble, Mother?

1096
01:18:07,892 --> 01:18:10,394
Or should I even call you that?

1097
01:18:11,646 --> 01:18:14,524
Oh, Rapunzel,
do you even hear yourself?

1098
01:18:14,565 --> 01:18:17,276
Why would you ask
such a ridiculous question?

1099
01:18:17,360 --> 01:18:20,822
It was you! It was all you!

1100
01:18:22,907 --> 01:18:26,410
Everything I did was to protect you.

1101
01:18:27,745 --> 01:18:28,996
-(GRUNTS)
- Rapunzel!

1102
01:18:29,080 --> 01:18:32,083
I've spent my entire life
hiding from people

1103
01:18:32,166 --> 01:18:34,502
-who would use me for my power...
- Rapunzel!

1104
01:18:34,585 --> 01:18:37,588
...when I should have been hiding
from you!

1105
01:18:37,672 --> 01:18:40,967
Where will you go?
He won't be there for you.

1106
01:18:41,050 --> 01:18:42,927
<i>RAPUNZEL: What did you do to him?</i>

1107
01:18:43,427 --> 01:18:46,681
<i>GOTHEL: That criminal is to be hanged
for his crimes.</i>

1108
01:18:46,764 --> 01:18:50,184
-(GASPS) No.
- Now, now, it's all right.

1109
01:18:50,268 --> 01:18:54,856
Listen to me.
All of this is as it should be.

1110
01:18:55,273 --> 01:18:58,776
No! You were wrong about the world.

1111
01:18:59,318 --> 01:19:01,821
And you were wrong about me!

1112
01:19:01,904 --> 01:19:05,950
And I will never
let you use my hair again!

1113
01:19:05,992 --> 01:19:07,034
(GRUNTS)

1114
01:19:10,288 --> 01:19:11,831
(PANTING)

1115
01:19:15,084 --> 01:19:17,587
(SOFTLY) You want me
to be the bad guy?

1116
01:19:17,628 --> 01:19:21,465
Fine, now I'm the bad guy.

1117
01:19:23,718 --> 01:19:25,094
(GRUNTING)

1118
01:19:35,646 --> 01:19:37,273
What's this?

1119
01:19:37,315 --> 01:19:39,150
Open up!

1120
01:19:40,193 --> 01:19:42,278
- What's the password?
- What?

1121
01:19:42,320 --> 01:19:44,614
-(CHUCKLING) Nope.
- Open this door!

1122
01:19:44,655 --> 01:19:46,490
Not even close!

1123
01:19:46,657 --> 01:19:49,410
You have three seconds! One...

1124
01:19:50,328 --> 01:19:51,704
Two...

1125
01:19:53,623 --> 01:19:54,665
Three.

1126
01:19:56,542 --> 01:19:57,752
Huh?

1127
01:20:00,213 --> 01:20:02,381
Frying pans! Who knew, right?

1128
01:20:02,465 --> 01:20:04,008
(THUDDING)

1129
01:20:05,676 --> 01:20:07,178
(ALL YELLING)

1130
01:20:17,855 --> 01:20:20,149
(BELLOWING)

1131
01:20:20,191 --> 01:20:21,275
(ALL SCREAMING)

1132
01:20:25,696 --> 01:20:27,365
(PANTING)

1133
01:20:27,448 --> 01:20:28,658
(SOLDIERS YELLING)

1134
01:20:31,994 --> 01:20:33,287
- Head down.
- Head down.

1135
01:20:33,371 --> 01:20:34,455
- Arms in.
- Arms in.

1136
01:20:34,538 --> 01:20:36,207
- Knees apart.
- Knees apart. Knees apart?

1137
01:20:37,375 --> 01:20:39,168
Why do I need
to keep my knees apart...

1138
01:20:40,503 --> 01:20:43,798
(SCREAMING)

1139
01:20:44,799 --> 01:20:45,841
(EXHALES)

1140
01:20:45,883 --> 01:20:46,884
(NICKERS)

1141
01:20:47,385 --> 01:20:50,596
Max! You brought them here?

1142
01:20:52,807 --> 01:20:53,849
Thank you.

1143
01:20:53,975 --> 01:20:55,059
(NEIGHS)

1144
01:20:55,268 --> 01:20:57,895
No, really. Thank you.

1145
01:20:59,814 --> 01:21:01,148
I feel maybe this whole time,

1146
01:21:01,232 --> 01:21:03,150
we've just been misunderstanding
one another,

1147
01:21:03,234 --> 01:21:04,944
and we're really just...

1148
01:21:05,319 --> 01:21:06,612
You're right, we should go.

1149
01:21:11,951 --> 01:21:14,078
(SOLDIERS YELLING)

1150
01:21:14,245 --> 01:21:15,288
Max?

1151
01:21:16,414 --> 01:21:17,498
Max!

1152
01:21:18,124 --> 01:21:19,583
- Max!
-(NEIGHING)

1153
01:21:19,667 --> 01:21:22,795
(SCREAMING)

1154
01:21:24,338 --> 01:21:26,132
(NEIGHING)

1155
01:21:27,425 --> 01:21:28,426
(WOMAN EXCLAIMS)

1156
01:21:29,051 --> 01:21:32,221
Okay, Max.
Let's see how fast you can run.

1157
01:21:51,532 --> 01:21:52,700
Rapunzel?

1158
01:21:54,702 --> 01:21:56,287
Rapunzel, let down your hair!

1159
01:22:12,011 --> 01:22:14,430
Rapunzel,
I thought I'd never see you again.

1160
01:22:14,472 --> 01:22:15,514
Huh?

1161
01:22:15,639 --> 01:22:17,683
(SCREAMING MUFFLED WARNING)

1162
01:22:18,017 --> 01:22:19,518
-(GRUNTS)
-(GROANS)

1163
01:22:20,394 --> 01:22:21,395
(MUFFLED SCREAM)

1164
01:22:23,105 --> 01:22:26,025
Now look what you've done, Rapunzel.

1165
01:22:26,108 --> 01:22:30,446
Oh, don't worry, dear.
Our secret will die with him.

1166
01:22:30,529 --> 01:22:32,114
(MUFFLED PROTESTS)

1167
01:22:32,156 --> 01:22:33,783
GOTHEL: And as for us...

1168
01:22:33,949 --> 01:22:35,034
(SCOFFS)

1169
01:22:35,117 --> 01:22:39,747
We are going where no one
will ever find you again.

1170
01:22:39,914 --> 01:22:41,123
(MUFFLED SCREAMS)

1171
01:22:41,165 --> 01:22:42,166
(SNARLING)

1172
01:22:43,584 --> 01:22:45,711
-(GOTHEL GRUNTS)
-(SQUEAKS)

1173
01:22:45,795 --> 01:22:47,463
Rapunzel, really!

1174
01:22:48,297 --> 01:22:51,926
Enough already! Stop fighting me!

1175
01:22:52,551 --> 01:22:54,637
No! I won't stop!

1176
01:22:54,678 --> 01:22:57,890
For every minute of the rest of my life,
I will fight!

1177
01:22:57,973 --> 01:23:01,852
I will never stop trying
to get away from you!

1178
01:23:02,061 --> 01:23:03,354
(PANTING)

1179
01:23:04,271 --> 01:23:08,818
But if you let me save him,
I will go with you.

1180
01:23:09,568 --> 01:23:12,530
(GRUNTING) No! No, Rapunzel.

1181
01:23:13,406 --> 01:23:16,700
I'll never run. I'll never try to escape.

1182
01:23:16,742 --> 01:23:20,371
Just let me heal him
and you and I will be together,

1183
01:23:20,413 --> 01:23:22,498
forever, just like you want.

1184
01:23:22,540 --> 01:23:24,542
Everything will be the way it was.

1185
01:23:25,876 --> 01:23:27,002
I promise.

1186
01:23:27,920 --> 01:23:29,713
Just like you want.

1187
01:23:32,716 --> 01:23:36,053
(ENUNCIATING) Just let me heal him.

1188
01:23:41,600 --> 01:23:44,979
In case you get any ideas
about following us.

1189
01:23:45,062 --> 01:23:46,730
(couemwe)

1190
01:23:47,064 --> 01:23:48,274
Eugene!

1191
01:23:48,566 --> 01:23:49,608
(couemwe)

1192
01:23:49,692 --> 01:23:51,068
(GROANING)

1193
01:23:55,197 --> 01:23:57,616
I'm so sorry.
Everything is going to be okay, though.

1194
01:23:57,700 --> 01:23:58,742
No, Rapunzel.

1195
01:23:58,784 --> 01:24:02,204
I promise. You have to trust me.
Come on. Just breathe.

1196
01:24:02,246 --> 01:24:03,914
I can't let you do this.

1197
01:24:04,582 --> 01:24:06,709
And I can't let you die.

1198
01:24:07,251 --> 01:24:10,921
But if you do then you will die.

1199
01:24:11,005 --> 01:24:14,717
Hey. It's going to be all right.

1200
01:24:19,930 --> 01:24:21,098
(WEAKLY) Rapunzel.

1201
01:24:22,016 --> 01:24:23,142
Wait.

1202
01:24:32,067 --> 01:24:33,319
Eugene...

1203
01:24:34,278 --> 01:24:35,446
No!

1204
01:24:40,367 --> 01:24:41,619
(BLUBBERING)

1205
01:24:42,286 --> 01:24:43,287
(SHRIEKS)

1206
01:24:43,621 --> 01:24:47,249
What have you done?
What have you done?

1207
01:24:48,501 --> 01:24:49,627
No!

1208
01:24:53,214 --> 01:24:55,466
No!No.No!

1209
01:24:55,799 --> 01:25:00,095
(SOBBING)

1210
01:25:03,057 --> 01:25:04,308
(EXCLAIMING)

1211
01:25:05,309 --> 01:25:08,479
(SCREAMING)

1212
01:25:20,991 --> 01:25:23,744
(PANTING)

1213
01:25:23,994 --> 01:25:25,329
(GASPS)

1214
01:25:26,163 --> 01:25:28,040
No,no,no.Eugene.

1215
01:25:29,500 --> 01:25:30,709
(COUGHS)

1216
01:25:30,793 --> 01:25:35,172
No! Look at me. I'm right here.
Don't go. Stay with me.

1217
01:25:35,756 --> 01:25:38,842
<i>(SINGING) Flower, gleam and glow
Let your power shine</i>

1218
01:25:38,926 --> 01:25:41,845
<i>Make the clock reverse
Bring back what once was mine</i>

1219
01:25:41,929 --> 01:25:43,013
Rapunzel.

1220
01:25:43,430 --> 01:25:44,515
What?

1221
01:25:48,185 --> 01:25:50,062
(WEAKLY) You were my new dream.

1222
01:25:51,021 --> 01:25:52,314
(CHUCKLES SADLY)

1223
01:25:53,357 --> 01:25:55,109
And you were mine.

1224
01:26:00,114 --> 01:26:01,282
(EXHALES)

1225
01:26:21,468 --> 01:26:24,972
<i>(SINGING) Heal what has been hurt</i>

1226
01:26:26,390 --> 01:26:30,019
<i>Change the Fates' design</i>

1227
01:26:31,061 --> 01:26:34,148
<i>Save what has been lost</i>

1228
01:26:36,775 --> 01:26:39,612
<i>Bring back what once was mine</i>

1229
01:26:43,073 --> 01:26:45,034
<i>What once was mine</i>

1230
01:26:47,244 --> 01:26:50,122
(SOBBING)

1231
01:27:40,631 --> 01:27:41,882
(EXHALES)

1232
01:27:42,508 --> 01:27:43,967
Rapunzel?

1233
01:27:44,093 --> 01:27:46,345
(GASPS) Eugene?

1234
01:27:48,389 --> 01:27:51,350
Did I ever tell you
I've got a thing for brunettes?

1235
01:27:51,642 --> 01:27:52,935
(LAUGHS)

1236
01:27:53,560 --> 01:27:54,770
Eugene!

1237
01:27:54,812 --> 01:27:56,063
(LAUGHING)

1238
01:27:57,815 --> 01:27:59,650
(CRYING)

1239
01:29:15,976 --> 01:29:17,519
(LAUGHING SOFTLY)

1240
01:29:32,910 --> 01:29:33,911
(GASPS)

1241
01:29:34,286 --> 01:29:37,581
<i>FLYNN". Well, you can imagine
what happened next.</i>

1242
01:29:40,042 --> 01:29:43,629
<i>The kingdom rejoiced,
for their lost princess had returned.</i>

1243
01:29:43,712 --> 01:29:48,425
<i>The party lasted an entire week, and
honestly I don't remember most of it.</i>

1244
01:29:49,259 --> 01:29:51,094
<i>Dreams came true all over the place.</i>

1245
01:29:51,136 --> 01:29:54,431
<i>That guy went on to become the most
famous concert pianist in the world,</i>

1246
01:29:54,515 --> 01:29:56,183
<i>if you can believe it!</i>

1247
01:29:57,768 --> 01:30:01,146
<i>And this guy?
He eventually found true love.</i>

1248
01:30:02,105 --> 01:30:06,276
<i>As for this guy, I assume he's happy.
He's never told me otherwise.</i>

1249
01:30:07,444 --> 01:30:08,445
(NEIGHS SHARPLY)

1250
01:30:08,487 --> 01:30:09,613
<i>Thanks to Maximus,</i>

1251
01:30:09,655 --> 01:30:12,741
<i>crime in the kingdom
disappeared almost overnight.</i>

1252
01:30:12,866 --> 01:30:14,034
(GRUNTS)

1253
01:30:14,284 --> 01:30:16,328
<i>As did most of the apples.</i>

1254
01:30:18,080 --> 01:30:20,958
<i>Pascal never changed.</i>

1255
01:30:25,045 --> 01:30:29,049
<i>At last Rapunzel was home.
And she finally had a real family.</i>

1256
01:30:30,801 --> 01:30:33,428
<i>She was a princess worth waiting for.</i>

1257
01:30:33,470 --> 01:30:36,974
<i>Beloved by all, she led her kingdom
with all the grace and wisdom</i>

1258
01:30:37,015 --> 01:30:38,475
<i>that her parents did before her.</i>

1259
01:30:39,810 --> 01:30:42,980
<i>And, as for me,
I started going by Eugene again,</i>

1260
01:30:43,021 --> 01:30:45,148
<i>stopped thieving
and turned it all around.</i>

1261
01:30:45,232 --> 01:30:47,818
<i>But I know what the big question is.</i>

1262
01:30:47,860 --> 01:30:50,028
<i>Did Rapunzel and I ever get married?</i>

1263
01:30:50,112 --> 01:30:51,238
<i>I'm pleased to tell you</i>

1264
01:30:51,321 --> 01:30:55,701
<i>that after years and years
of asking and asking and asking...</i>

1265
01:30:57,828 --> 01:30:59,705
<i>I finally said yes.</i>

1266
01:30:59,788 --> 01:31:04,084
<i>RAPUNZEL'. (SCOLDMG) Eugene.
FLYNN". All right, I asked her.</i>

1267
01:31:04,167 --> 01:31:06,628
<i>RAPUNZEL". And we're living
happily ever after.</i>

1268
01:31:07,296 --> 01:31:08,755
FLYNN: Yes, <i>we</i> are.

1269
